<div id="pf42" class="pf w8 hf" data-page-no="42"><div class="pc pc42 w8 hf"><img class="bi x0 y0 w9 h10" alt="" src="bg42.png"/><div class="t m371 xb h12 ya2c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m6e2 xd h12 y384 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Levitical order had a line of priests but the new order has </div><div class="t m28 x45 h12 ya2d ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m2d7 xc9 h12 ya2d ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">only </div><div class="t m28 x35 h12 ya2d ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m512 x28 h12 y386 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">priest (verses 23, 24). </div><div class="t m373 xb h12 ya2e ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m176 x53 h12 ya2f ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Under the new order Christ continues </div><div class="t m28 x13 h12 y388 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1d9 xdb h12 ya30 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 24). </div><div class="t m374 xb h12 y38a ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m1e9 x53 h12 ya31 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Under this order Christ is able to </div><div class="t m28 x32 h12 ya31 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m2b7 x7c h12 y688 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 25). </div><div class="t m6b4 xb h12 ya32 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m647 x53 h12 y9db ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">As priest of the new order Christ is </div><div class="t m28 x31 h12 y38c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1d9 xdb h12 ya33 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 26). </div><div class="t m341 xb h12 y8 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t me7 x53 h12 y8 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ has no need to offer </div><div class="t m28 xb0 h12 y8 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m1d9 xdb h12 y68a ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 27). </div><div class="t m6c6 xb h12 y38f ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t m345 x53 h12 ya34 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mortals served as priests under the Levitical system but Christ is </div><div class="t m9b x53 h12 y2d4 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">consecrated </div><div class="t m28 x16 h12 y2d4 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t mda xdb h12 ya35 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verse 28). </div><div class="t m3e1 x44 h12 ya36 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">FURTHER STUDY AND MEDITATION: </div><div class="t m4ad xb h12 yc5 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read </div><div class="t m1b8 x64 h12 yc5 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Early Writings, </div><div class="t m6e3 x19 h12 ya37 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pages 250-256. </div><div class="t m6e4 xb h12 ya38 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The record tells us nothing about his [Melchizedek&apos;s] pedigree, his </div><div class="t m6e5 x44 h12 y7a ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">birth, or death. So far as the record goes, no beginning nor end of life is </div><div class="t m194 x5e h12 y37d ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">given; and it was the custom, therefore, among the Jews, to speak of such </div><div class="t m3d1 x5e h12 y37f ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as having no genealogy, no mother, no father, no beginning of days, nor </div><div class="t m3d3 x5e h12 ya39 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">end of life. And considering that all these expressions are used simply </div><div class="t m92 x5e h12 ya3a ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">from the standpoint of the record, there is no difficulty. Melchizedek sud-</div><div class="t m53a x44 h12 ya3b ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">denly appears upon the scene of action, an eminent servant of God, com-</div><div class="t m609 x44 h12 ya3c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bining, in his own person the double office of king and priest. All before </div><div class="t mff x44 h12 ya3d ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">him is blank; all following him is blank. Neither birth nor death appearing </div><div class="t m558 x5e h12 ya3e ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in the scene, he becomes a fitting prototype of Christ in his position of </div><div class="t mb x44 h12 ya3f ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">priest-king in this dispensation.&quot;—Uriah Smith, </div><div class="t m5b4 x8 h12 ya40 ff6 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Review and Herald, </div><div class="t m68c x44 h12 ya41 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Nov. 5, 1895. </div><div class="t m4b7 x5e h12 y862 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SUMMARY: The knowledge that we have a merciful, compassionate High </div><div class="t m1c1 x44 h12 ya42 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Priest in heaven gives us strong confidence. He is the one and only true </div><div class="t m15c x44 h12 ya43 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Priest; His priesthood is superior to every other priesthood, the Levitical </div><div class="t m55e x44 h12 ya44 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">order included. We need no other mediator, no human priest. </div><div class="t m312 x62 h12 y297 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">APPLICATION: </div><div class="t m192 x5e h12 ya45 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m12c x63 h12 y9f4 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What difference does it make to me to know that I have &quot;such an high </div><div class="t m250 xb h12 ya46 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">priest&quot;? Consider, for example, does it make a difference: when I feel </div><div class="t m3e7 xb h12 ya47 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">discouraged? in my concept of heaven? in my hour of test? </div><div class="t m192 x5e h12 y83f ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m524 x63 h12 ya48 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sometimes we feel lonely and wonder if anyone cares. Do the ideas </div><div class="t m4eb xb h12 ya49 ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">presented in this lesson suggest where I can find help? </div><div class="t m192 x5e h12 ya4a ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">o </div><div class="t m41c x63 h12 ya4b ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How can I make the marvelous truths of this lesson real to others? </div><div class="t m688 x44 h12 ya4c ff3 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES: </div><div class="t m245 x62 hc y9fc ff1 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">62 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
